What is a Shell

The shell is a programm that takes input from the keyboard and gives the operating system to perform. Before  the advent of GUI is the shell.

What is a Terminal

Its a program called a terminal emulator. This program opens a window and lets you interact with the shell.

What is shebang 
is the character sequence consisting of the characters number sign and exclamation mark (#!) at the beginning of a script

Type of commands

An executable program : located in usr/bin, program such as compiled binaries written in c, c++ shell, perl python

shell bultin :internally commands - cd

shell function : shell script, and shell funcitons

An alias : commands built from other commands.

which, type, help

wc -l file : to check number of lines in a file
